    	<h1 class="w3-xxlarge"><span class="w3-hide-small">Michael Lengefeld | </span>ICE, COVID, BLM, and Blowback</h1>
	</header>
	
<body>
	<div class="example w3-row">
	<div class="w3-half w3-container">
	<h1>What you need to know</h1>
		<h2>Enforcement first immigration policies are justified on racist and nativist grounds—to protect and insulate the 
    larger society from the “threat” posed by nonwhite immigrants. This nativist imagery suggests that risks are— similar 
    to the people detained in them— confined by the walls and fences that surround ICE facilities. However, this is a fantasy.
    The COVID-19 pandemic brought the blow back of nativist and racist immigration policy into sharp relief. Instead of making
    the United States safer, ICE detention facilities altered the riskscape and increased the risk of infection for the 
    residents of nearby communities and counties. 
		</h2>
	</div>
	<div class="w3-half w3-container">
		<br>
		<figure class="item">
    		<img src="/img/predatordrone.jpg" alt="American Reaper Drone" style="width:100%; height: 100%; border:1px solid black">
